# funkysi1701.com (Hugo blog) — Cursor rules (repository)

These rules apply to all edits in this repo. Prefer matching existing patterns (Hugo TOML front matter in `+++` fences, site overrides under root `layouts/` and `static/`, and the conventions already used in `content/`).

## Source of truth and generated output

- **Hugo content and config:** Edit Markdown under `content/`, site parameters under `config/_default/` (and environment-specific `config/development/`, `config/staging/`, `config/production/` when the change is environment-specific). The active theme is set in `config/_default/config.toml` (`theme = 'hugo-theme-bootstrap'`).
- **Theme vs site overrides:** Prefer fixing or extending behaviour via root `layouts/`, `assets/`, and `static/` so upstream `themes/hugo-theme-bootstrap/` stays easy to update. If you must edit the vendored theme, keep the diff minimal and intentional.
- **Build output:** `public/` is generated by Hugo and is not the source of truth. Production builds use Dockerized Hugo with `--minify --environment production` (see `.github/workflows/azure-static-web-apps-victorious-pebble-0b8f90e03.yml`). After substantive template or asset changes, run a local `hugo` build (or `hugo server -D` for iteration) so failures surface before push.
- **Git submodules:** CI checks out with `submodules: true`. If this repo uses submodules in future, keep their configuration in sync and ensure the site still builds cleanly.
- **Azure Static Web Apps:** `staticwebapp.config.json` at the repo root is copied into `public/` during deploy; keep routing and headers aligned with how the built site is actually served.
- **Kubernetes / Helm:** Container image build, ECR push, and Helm deploys are orchestrated in **`azure-pipelines.yml`** (`Helm/blog/`). When you change infra or env URLs, consider **develop**, **test**, and **main** namespaces and both hosting paths (SWA and cluster).

## Security and configuration

- This repo intentionally tracks `.env` for non-secret shared configuration such as `HUGO_VERSION`. **Do not** put secrets in `.env` or commit API keys, credentials, or deployment tokens. The Azure Static Web Apps deploy token is **only** for GitHub Actions secrets—do not embed it in the repo.
- **Giscus** and similar integrations use public repo identifiers in config; still avoid pasting private tokens or unrelated secrets into `config/` or front matter.

## Frontend, assets, and local development

- **Local dev:** `hugo server -D` from the repo root, or Docker Compose (`docker-compose.yml`) / the Hugo image command documented in `README.md`. Hugo version for Docker and CI comes from `HUGO_VERSION` in `.env`.
- **Images:** Put static binaries under `static/` (served from site root). Prefer descriptive file names and stable paths so external links do not rot.
- **Node tooling:** `package.json` supports Playwright tests and theme-related scripts. After changing `package.json` or `package-lock.json`, run **`npm ci`** locally (matches Azure DevOps and keeps `node_modules` consistent) before **`npm test`**.

## SEO and meta (aligned with CI)

- **Blog posts (`content/posts/**/*.md`):** Front matter `title` must stay within **50–60 characters** (inclusive), and `description` within **110–160 characters** (inclusive). CI enforces this via `scripts/check_meta_titles.py` and `scripts/check_meta_descriptions.py` (`.github/workflows/meta-title-length.yml` and `meta-description-length.yml`). Fix out-of-range values before merge.
- **Headings:** Use a single top-level Markdown heading per page where that matches the site’s heading structure (one primary in-page title). Use lower-level headings for sections.
- **Open Graph / Twitter / JSON-LD:** Follow patterns the theme and existing `layouts/partials/head.html` (and related partials) already emit. When adding share imagery or new external hosts, ensure CSP, headers, and SWA config remain coherent—do not bolt on inline trackers or third-party scripts without a clear need and review.
- **Language:** Site language is British English (`languageCode = 'en-gb'` in config); keep copy and spelling consistent unless a quoted source requires otherwise.

## Testing and CI expectations

- **`npm test`** runs Playwright (`@playwright/test`) against **`playwright.config.ts`**. Set **`BASE_URL`** when the target is not production (for example `http://localhost:1313` for `hugo server -D`); if unset, tests use **`https://www.funkysi1701.com`**. Install browsers when needed: `npx playwright install chromium`.
- **Primary E2E gate:** **`azure-pipelines-playwright.yml`** (Azure DevOps) runs the full suite on PRs and branch pushes, choosing **`BASE_URL`** from the branch: **`main`** or **`master`** → production; **`develop`** → **`https://blog-dev.funkysi1701.com`**; otherwise production. It runs **`scripts/generate-page-coverage.js`** and can upload to **Codecov** when **`CODECOV_TOKEN`** is set. **GitHub Actions** does meta checks and SWA deploy but **does not** run Playwright today—do not assume a green GHA run implies E2E passed unless a workflow is added later.
- **Specs:** Scenario docs live under **`specs/`** (notably **`specs/funkysi1701-test-plan.md`**). Many tests reference them with a leading **`// spec: specs/...`** comment—keep plans and tests aligned when behaviour changes.
- **Branches (deploy / integration):** **`main`** → production (GitHub Actions → Azure Static Web Apps; Azure Pipelines → ECR → Helm **`main`**). **`develop`** → non-prod (Helm **`develop`** and **`test`** namespaces; blog-dev / blog-test). **`feature/*`** → build and Helm to **`develop`** only. **`.github/workflows/auto-pr.yml`** can open or refresh **develop → main**. There is no **`dev`** branch; use **`develop`** for integration.
- **Meta length checks:** Run the Python scripts locally if you touch post front matter: `python scripts/check_meta_titles.py --root .` and `python scripts/check_meta_descriptions.py --root .` (same checks as **`.github/workflows/meta-title-length.yml`** and **`meta-description-length.yml`**).
- **Links:** A scheduled broken-link workflow hits a fixed list of production URLs (`.github/workflows/link.yml`). Prefer stable permalinks; if you rename or remove high-traffic paths, consider whether that list (or redirects in `staticwebapp.config.json`) needs updating.

## Accessibility

- **Alt text:** Every meaningful image in Markdown must use `![descriptive alt text](...)`. Use empty alt only for purely decorative images. For HTML partials or shortcodes that emit `<img>`, include appropriate `alt` (or equivalent ARIA) attributes.

## Documentation (Markdown)

- Tracked **`*.md`** files are part of the repo contract. When a change affects anything they describe (Hugo commands, Docker, CI, env vars, deploy steps, or testing), **update every affected Markdown file in the same change** so commands and paths stay accurate.
- At minimum, keep **`README.md`** and **`.github/copilot-instructions.md`** aligned with real behaviour when workflows, branches, or testing shift; search for other **`*.md`** mentions of the same topic and fix stale references.
- Do **not** add new Markdown files unless the user or task explicitly asks for them; prefer updating existing docs.

## Scope of changes

- Make the smallest change that satisfies the task. Do not refactor unrelated templates, rename unrelated identifiers, or add dependencies without a clear need.
